{{notability|date=March 2015}}{{refimprove|date=April 2015}} {{Infobox court case |name = McComb v. Connaghan |court = |image = |imagesize = |imagelink = |imagealt = |caption = |full name = McComb Family v. Phillip Connaghan |date decided = <!-- {{Start date|yyyy|mm|dd|df=}} --> |citations = |transcripts = |judges = |number of judges = |decision by = |dissenting = |prior actions = |appealed from = |appealed to = |subsequent actions = |related actions = |opinions = |keywords = <!-- {{Flatlist|}} --> |italic title = }}
'''''McComb v. Connaghan''''' was a court case in [[Denver]], [[Colorado]] in which Phillip Connaghan was held liable for the wrongful death of Michael McComb who was killed by a [[Spring-gun|shotgun booby trap]].
==External links== *[https://www.nytimes.com/1990/08/22/us/booby-trap-death-brings-fine.html Booby Trap Death Brings Fine]
